description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for highly motivated Registered Nurses to join our Community Diabetes Nursing Team working within Wrightington , Wigan and Leigh Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working independently and as part of the multidisciplinary team you will work as Diabetes Specialist Nurses in providing a progressive, innovative service for patient with diabetes enabling them to self-manage their condition. To do this you will be undertaking Nurse led clinics and home visits. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an opportunity to make a real difference to the lives of patients diagnosed with diabetes. We are a team that supports the development of all HCP and encourage our team to progress their own development .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To undertake this role the successful candidate should have extensive experience of working with patients with diabetes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are 2 posts available - 1 full time (37.5 hours) and 1 part time (30 hours). Both posts will work across a variety of shifts Monday to Friday. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will require work across all areas of the Trust, including those designated as positive, asymptomatic and negative COVID areas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An Enhanced DBS (with check against the Adults Barred list) will be required for the role and one will be obtained for the successful candidates during pre-employment checks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name - Steven Lowe&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title - Health Intergration Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address - Steven.lowe2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number - via Departmental PA 01942 483506&lt;/p&gt;
